50|$|<b>Flax</b> mills for <b>spinning</b> flaxen yarn {{were invented}} by John Kendrew and Thomas Porthouse of Darlington, England, in 1787. New methods of {{processing}} flax {{have led to}} renewed interest {{in the use of}} flax as an industrial fiber.|$|R
